==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pipsissewa
<hw>Pip*sis"se*wa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From American
Indian.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A low evergreen plant
(<spn>Chimaphila umbellata</spn>), with narrow, wedge-lanceolate leaves,
and an umbel of pretty nodding fragrant blossoms. It has been used in
nephritic diseases. Called also <altname>prince's
pine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pipy</ent>⟦br⟧
